---
description: Best practices for asynchronous HTTP requests with aiohttp
globs: **/*.{py}
---
 Use `async with` for proper resource management and connection pooling.
- Implement timeouts with `ClientTimeout` to prevent hanging requests.
- Use `aiohttp.ClientSession` for multiple requests to share connection pool.
- Leverage `aiohttp_jinja2` for server-side rendering of HTML templates.
- Handle exceptions with `try/except` blocks to manage network errors gracefully.